apierror-wikibaselexeme-form-must-have-a:
{{doc-apierror|wikibaselexeme}}
API error message that is being reported when no lexicographical Form representations were provided
apierror-wikibaselexeme-form-not-found:
{{doc-apierror|wikibaselexeme}}
API error message that is being reported when lexicographical Form with provided ID does not exist.

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the field
* $2 - ID of the lexicographical Form
apierror-wikibaselexeme-invalid-form-cla:
{{doc-apierror|wikibaselexeme}}
API error message that is being reported when a Lexeme's Form's claims field is invalid. 

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the parameter that is expected to be a list of serialized claims.
* $2 - Path of the field inside of the JSON object (e.g "array-field-name/0/other-field-name")
apierror-wikibaselexeme-invalid-item-id:
{{doc-apierror|wikibaselexeme}}
API error message that is being reported when the language of a lexeme term contains an unknown item id.
apierror-wikibaselexeme-invalid-sense-cl:
{{doc-apierror|wikibaselexeme}}
API error message that is being reported when a Lexeme's Sense's claims field is invalid. 

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the parameter that is expected to be a list of serialized claims.
* $2 - Path of the field inside of the JSON object (e.g "array-field-name/0/other-field-name")
apierror-wikibaselexeme-json-field-has-w:
{{doc-apierror|wikibaselexeme}}
API error message that is being reported when field in JSON object expected to be of certain type, but value of another type was provided. 

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the parameter that is expected to be JSON object.
* $2 - Path of the field inside of the JSON object (e.g "array-field-name/0/other-field-name")
* $3 - Expected type name (e.g. string, array, object) 
* $4 - Provided value type name
apierror-wikibaselexeme-json-field-not-i:
{{doc-apierror|wikibaselexeme}}
API error message that is being reported when field in JSON object expected to contain serialized Item ID, but contains something else. 

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the parameter that is expected to be JSON object.
* $2 - Path of the field inside of the JSON object (e.g "array-field-name/0/other-field-name")
* $3 - Provided value
apierror-wikibaselexeme-json-field-requi:
{{doc-apierror|wikibaselexeme}}
API error message that is being reported when required field in JSON object is not present. 

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the parameter that is expected to be JSON object. 
* $2 - Path of the field inside of the JSON object (e.g "array-field-name/0/other-field-name")
apierror-wikibaselexeme-language-inconsi:
{{doc-apierror|wikibaselexeme}}
API error message that is being reported when language of provided representation or lemma is inconsistent.

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the parameter that is expected to be JSON object.
* $2 - Path of the field inside of the JSON object (e.g "array-field-name/0/other-field-name")
* $3 - Expected language
* $4 - Given language
apierror-wikibaselexeme-lexeme-not-found:
{{doc-apierror|wikibaselexeme}}
API error message that is being reported when Lexeme with provided ID does not exist.

Parameters:
* $1 - Name of the field
* $2 - ID of the Lexeme
apierror-wikibaselexeme-lexeme-term-lang:
{{doc-apierror|wikibaselexeme}}
API error message that is being reported when the language of one of provided representations or lemmas is empty
apierror-wikibaselexeme-lexeme-term-text:
{{doc-apierror|wikibaselexeme}}
API error message that is being reported when one of provided representations or lemmas is empty
apierror-wikibaselexeme-parameter-invali:

API error message that is being reported when provided data parameter is not a valid JSON

apierror-wikibaselexeme-unknown-language:
{{doc-apierror|wikibaselexeme}}
API error message that is being reported when the language field contains an unknown language.

* $1 - field name
* $2 - path
* $3 - language code

{{doc-apierror|wikibaselexeme}}
API error message that is being reported when the language field contains an unknown language. Like {{msg-mw|apierror-wikibaselexeme-unknown-language}} but with added text to which the language code should apply.

* $1 - field name
* $2 - path
* $3 - language code
* $4 - the text of the term
